text.section:
The local law may regulate:
the location, height, bulk, and size of each building or other structure, and any unit in the building or structure;
building lines;
minimum frontage;
the depth and area of each lot; and
the percentage of a lot that may be occupied;
the size of lots, yards, courts, and other open spaces;
the construction of temporary stands and structures;
the density and distribution of population;
the location and uses of buildings and structures and any units in those buildings and structures for:
trade;
industry;
residential purposes;
recreation;
agriculture;
public activities; and
other purposes; and
the uses of land, including surface, subsurface, and air rights for the land, for building or for any of the purposes described in item (5) of this subsection.
